node.text:
Ralph likes: reading books, stretching, talking on the phone, eating grass and not being killed for the cosmetic industry. 

Ralph called me about 12 months ago and asked if I would tell his story. I’m so grateful that he did and for all the wonderful people who helped make that possible especially @hsiglobal for the tireless work they do for the voiceless. 

Animal testing isn’t just cruel, it’s outdated. The practices used in cosmetic testing now were developed in 1940 – over 80 years ago. Let’s change that today! Please join me in supporting @hsigolbal to outlaw cosmetic animal testing once and for all. Go to hsi.org/SaveRalph and simply click a few buttons. Ralph and many other animals like him thank you in advance

Video and caption by @spencersusser
Thank you @taikawaititi @rickygervais  @zacefron  @pom.klementieff  @oliviamunn  @officialtriciahelfer @livtennet + @archfilmstudio @tobiasfouracre  @tristanoliverbsc and a very special thank you to the rest of the wonderful team who helped make this film a reality. Please see credits at end 🐰 #SaveRalph"

⚠️WARNING: GRAPHIC CONTENT⚠️ PLEASE READ & SEE THE LINK IN OUR BIO — We at Karmagawa are proud to announce our newest project with filmmaker @amirzakeri because as Amir says: we are at a pivotal time in history for wildlife and the environment. Deforestation, degradation of coral reefs, animal abuse, poaching, and the list goes on. While this is happening, it’s easy to sit back and say “well someone else will fix it...” No, we must each do our part to help! I believe that social media is one of our most powerful tools and it’s right in the palm of our hands. With the tap of your finger you can share a video which can be seen around the world and directly influence people. More importantly, we are in dire need of more content creators producing meaningful content to help spread  awareness to these crucial issues and enact positive ACTION. The link in my bio doesn’t just take you to my new film course, it allows you to join this all-important movement, which encompasses a belief that we can inspire one another to make this world better. Click the link in the @karmagawa or @savethereef bio and let’s work together to change the world! #savetheplanet #contentcreator #karmagawa
Via @karmagawa

Such a skilled hunting session 🐻 If you’re looking for an epic wildlife experience, Alaska might just be the place for you to visit next. Known and loved for its diverse wildlife, Alaska is home to many species including grizzlies and black bears, wolfs, reindeers, dall sheep and bisons. Would you visit Alaska? 🐺🦌

📍Alaska, United States

🇺🇸 Video by @mikewolfel 

#Wildgeography

Wildfires have erupted around the world; the most devastating in Turkey. 😢 Italy, USA, Spain, France, Cyprus, Finland, Lebanon, Canada & Greece have also had terrible fires! There has been severe flooding in Germany, China, Italy, Belgium & Netherlands. Hail bigger than tennis balls has rained down in northern Italy, and it’s even snowed in Brazil!
The second largest river in South America, Paraná River, is currently suffering from a severe drought, and we’ve seen tornadoes in Czechia. 🙏🏽 🌎 😞

Please tag your friends, share this on your stories!

I’ve had countless messages my from wonderful Turkish followers today, asking to share this. To all of you, my thoughts are with you, your family and your friends. 🙏🏽
Caption by @earthfocus
